block content

  .ui.text.container.addBottomMargin
    br    
    p The concept and consequences of identity theft (submodule 1)          
    p Learn 4/4
    .ui.raised.segment
      h3.bold Examples of Identity Theft
      p There are several types of identity theft based on the information stolen and the harm caused. In this module, we give you three examples of identity theft.

      ul
        li
          p <u>Financial identity theft</u> involves any account that someone else opens or uses without your consent, for which you are financially liable. This could be a bank account, credit card account, subscription to any service, insurance, loan, and many else.

        li
          p <u>Tax-related identity theft</u> occurs when scammers use personal identifiable information to file a tax return to claim a fraudulent refund.

        li
          p <u>Medical identity theft</u> happens when scammers use personal identifiable information to submit fraudulent claims to Medicare or other health insurers without your authorization.
    
      #avatar.ui.one.column.centered.grid(style="margin: 50px")
        .ui.pointing.below.circular.label
          p(style="padding: 20px;") Most of the time, scammers steal information needed to make the account with data breaches or purchase from illegal trade with other scammers.
            br
            br
            | Please remember that there are numerous ways in which identity theft can occur other than these three types. You can check out AARPâ€™s Fraud Resources for more information about different types of scams.
        img.ui.small.image.right.floated(src='/images/avatar-pic.png')

    .div(style='margin-top:20px;')
      button.ui.large.button.left.floated(onclick="location.href='/identity_learn_page3';") 
        i.arrow.left.icon 
        | Back
      button.ui.large.button.left.floated(onclick="location.href='/';") Save & Exit
